  "description": "This mod adds the uncraft of the Potent Sulfur block, with 1x Potent Sulfur = 9x Sulfur [26.2-snapshot-1 +]",
  "body": "<div align=\"center\">\n  <h1>Potent Sulfur Rework</h1>\n  <br/>\n  <p>\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Release-1.2.x-limegreen\" alt=\"Release\">\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Minecraft-26.2_snapshot_1_to_6-blue?logo=data:image/png;base64,&logoWidth=50\" alt=\"Minecraft\">\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/License-CC_BY_4.0-blueviolet\" alt=\"License CC BY 4.0\">\n    <a href=\"https://discord.gg/77dJavp9\" target=\"_blank\">\n      <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/discord/1358706268012810350?color=5865F2&label=Discord&logo=discord&logoColor=white\" alt=\"Discord\">\n    </a>\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/modrinth/dt/77dJavp9?logo=modrinth&label=Modrinth\" alt=\"Modrinth\">\n  </p>\n</div>\n\n<br/>\n<br/>\n\n<h2>✨ Features</h2>\n<h3>🔥 Main description</h3>\n<blockquote>This feature allows players to uncraft one sulfur into nine smaller sulfur pieces. <br/>It introduces a simple and efficient way to break down sulfur for more flexible usage.</blockquote>\n\n<h3>⚙️ Use and benefits</h3>\n<blockquote>With this process, players can easily manage their sulfur resources and adapt quantities to their needs. <br/>It improves crafting precision and avoids wasting materials during recipes.</blockquote>\n\n<h3>🧩 Gameplay integration</h3>\n<blockquote>This system fits naturally into existing crafting mechanics. <br/>It encourages better resource management while expanding possibilities for sulfur-based crafting.</blockquote>\n\n<br/>\n\n<h2>🧪 Recipes</h2>\n<blockquote>\n  <img src=\"https://cdn.modrinth.com/data/77dJavp9/images/f10d79293116829921a83da53e570709bb3f8956.png\" alt=\"Uncraft of Potent Sulfur\">\n</blockquote>\n\n<br/>\n\n<h2>📥 Installation</h2>\n<h3>📁 Datapack</h3>\n<blockquote>\n  Drop the <code>.zip</code> file into your world's <code>datapacks</code> folder.<br/>\n  Reload the world or use <code>/reload</code>.<br/>\n  Enjoy your enchanted adventure!\n</blockquote>\n\n<h3>⚙️ Mod</h3>\n<blockquote>\n  Drop the <code>.jar</code> file into the <code>mods</code> folder of your instance.<br/>\n  <code>Restart</code> your game.<br/>\n  Have fun!\n</blockquote>",
